A husband has relived the horrifying 
moments he battled to save his wife as she drowned in 'hellish' waters 
while swimming in the Canary Islands.

Nicola Bate, 48, was dragged out to 
sea after she went for a swim off Famara Beach, near the resort of 
Caleta de Famara in Lanzarote.

On hearing her screams, Anthony Bate, 
56, left his children at a beach bar, and dashed out into the sea in a 
desperate attempt to rescue her.

He grabbed hold of her, but started to struggle in the strong riptide.

As he fought for his life he was rescued by a lifeguard and pulled to shore, only to discover his wife had died.

