Coroner Michael Singleton recorded a 
verdict of accidental death: 'Nicola Bate was overcome by water despite 
desperate attempts to save her.'

Mr Bate declined to comment after the hearing.

Nicola, who is originally from the village of Whalley in Lancashire was a housewife who also volunteered for the Home-Start charity.

The couple had met 20 years ago at an Asda store in Accrington and bonded over their mutual vegetarianism.

