'It was a little mistake with 
calamitous consequences and this is the tragedy we’re left with,' said 
Mr Bate. 'We are all devastated but we are being strong.'

Lanzarote, the easternmost of the Canary Islands, is one of the most popular destinations in Europe for British tourists.

Another British national died on the same beach in April after being pulled unconscious from the sea by fellow bathers.

The beach, on the island’s north coast, has become increasingly popular 
with surfers from around the world in recent years, according to local 
tourism websites.

